Interface to 'TensorFlow' Estimators  <https://www.tensorflow.org/programmers_guide/estimators>, a high-level  API that provides implementations of many different model types  including linear models and deep neural networks.

name: r-tfestimators
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.9.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-tfestimators
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/tfestimators_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/tfestimators/tfestimators_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 5bbe6e4dd05a32a6be033767d0e649ce2bf2092a8637a1fb66db2508d1a77ec8

build:
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-forge
    - r-magrittr
    - r-progress
    - r-purrr
    - r-reticulate >=1.10
    - r-rlang >=0.3
    - r-tensorflow >=1.9
    - r-tfruns >=1.1
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr
    - r-tidyselect
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-forge
    - r-magrittr
    - r-progress
    - r-purrr
    - r-reticulate >=1.10
    - r-rlang >=0.3
    - r-tensorflow >=1.9
    - r-tfruns >=1.1
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr
    - r-tidyselect

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('tfestimators')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('tfestimators')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/rstudio/tfestimators
  license: Apache-2.0
  summary: "Interface to 'TensorFlow' Estimators  <https://www.tensorflow.org/programmers_guide/estimators>, a high-level  API that provides implementations of many different model types  including linear models and deep neural networks. "
  license_family: APACHE
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - stevierene82
